@startuml Technical File Management â€” User Level
title Technical File (CRA Annex VII Documentation)

actor "User" as user
participant "Technical Files Page" as overview
participant "Product Detail" as detail
participant "Section Editor" as editor

== Viewing Technical File Overview ==

user -> overview : Navigates to /technical-files
user -> overview : Sees all products with\ncompleteness indicators\n(percentage per product)

== Editing a Section ==

user -> detail : Opens a product
user -> detail : Clicks "Technical File" tab
detail -> detail : Shows 8 CRA Annex VII sections:\n1. Product Description\n2. Design & Development\n3. Vulnerability Handling\n4. Risk Assessment\n5. Support Period\n6. Standards Applied\n7. Test Reports\n8. Declaration of Conformity

user -> detail : Clicks on a section
detail -> editor : Section opens with\nrich text editor
user -> editor : Types documentation content
user -> editor : Clicks "Save"
editor -> detail : Section saved,\ncompleteness updates

== Tracking Completeness ==

user -> detail : Sees completeness bar\nfor each section\n(filled / empty indicators)
note right of detail : All 8 sections must be\ncompleted for full CRA\ntechnical documentation\ncompliance.

== Viewing Across Products ==

user -> overview : Returns to /technical-files
user -> overview : Sees updated completeness\npercentages for all products
note right of overview : Quick overview of which\nproducts still need\ndocumentation work.

@enduml
